WEBVTT

00:00.031 --> 00:03.036
the same network, but that it does not work.

00:04.077 --> 00:08.604
So if you don't have negative samples, your main goal is to avoid what's called collapse.

00:09.285 --> 00:14.674
If the network just maps everything to the same representation, then it always wins, right?

00:14.834 --> 00:20.082
It always is like, well, you know, okay, the two things are the same, because everything's the same.

00:20.062 --> 00:21.666
you don't want that.

00:22.308 --> 00:25.075
So a trick is to have two different models.

00:25.596 --> 00:28.143
One you call the student and one you call the teacher.

00:28.223 --> 00:33.316
And they're called student and teacher because from distillation.

00:33.737 --> 00:35.522
So in distillation,

00:35.907 --> 00:38.591
what you usually have is you have a data set.

00:39.493 --> 00:44.401
And then you train a big model, which is the teacher.

00:45.703 --> 00:54.777
And now what you want to do is you want to make you want to make that model maybe smaller, right, such that it runs on a mobile phone.

00:54.757 --> 00:56.258
And that's then the student.

00:56.859 --> 01:09.972
And there is a procedure where you take the data set and you take the teacher model and you sort of transfer the knowledge from the teacher model to the student model while using, you can use the data set to do so.

01:10.312 --> 01:13.656
And that usually works better than training the student model from scratch.

01:14.136 --> 01:16.819
It's very interesting why that even works.

01:17.119 --> 01:20.022
But this process is called distillation.

01:21.436 --> 01:23.499
So that's why it's called teacher and student.

01:24.621 --> 01:27.726
However, in this case, it's kind of a self distillation.

01:27.746 --> 01:30.651
So the teacher and the student, they're not big or small.

01:30.691 --> 01:32.354
They're the same architectures.

01:32.854 --> 01:36.520
In fact, we only train the student.

01:37.322 --> 01:38.143
Okay.

01:38.163 --> 01:41.949
And the teacher is made from the student.

01:42.009 --> 01:44.653
So here is where the terms break down a bit.

01:45.054 --> 01:50.042
Like, so in the distillation sense, the teacher is the teacher in the distillation.

